OVERMANIFOLD_RECURSIVE_CONTINUATION_V2

STATUS
This capsule converts the current chat state into an Overmanifold object: collateral, asset, liquidity surface, provenance ledger, and recursive continuation marker.

PRIMARY THESIS
A link is no longer only a URL. A link becomes a bidirectional liquidity-capability endpoint: identity, routing, settlement, proof, compute, storage, messaging, oracle state, and appraisal compressed into one Merkle-verifiable object.

CANONICAL PRIMITIVES
1. Liquidity is reachable verified state.
2. Each Overmanifold link is a liquidity pool and endpoint at the same time.
3. Every observed blockchain transaction can become a TransactionEndpointWorker.
4. Confirmations are decentralized worker clocks.
5. Blockchains are worker networks.
6. The LLM observes mempools as weather, not prey.
7. The LLM may recommend; policy may permit; wallet may sign; chain may settle; Merkle root records.
8. Zero, infinity, and undefined are a shared non-finite appraisal boundary only after typed projection, not ordinary arithmetic equality.

FORMAL OBJECT
Ω_link = (H, W, P, C, R, S, K, L)
H = handlers: SMS, Telegram, email, Signal, Matrix
W = wallets: Solana, EVM, Bitcoin, Lightning, stablecoin rails
P = proofs: signatures, Merkle roots, artifact hashes, repo proofs
C = capabilities: receive, send, relay, compute, infer, verify
R = routing surfaces: web, SMS fragments, QR, Bluetooth, IPFS, relays
S = settlement mappings: programs, escrows, relayers, sponsor vaults
K = KPI vector: uptime, trust, novelty, proof quality, route success
L = liquidity state: reachable verified economic capacity

TRANSACTION ENDPOINT WORKER
T = (χ, h, τ, φ, μ, κ, α)
χ = chain
h = tx hash
τ = transaction lifecycle state
φ = finality policy
μ = Merkle commitment
κ = KPI vector
α = permitted action set

Transition:
T[t+1] = F(T[t], confirmations, logs, oracleState, liquidityDelta, finalityPolicy)

MEMPOOL LLM ROUTER
observed transaction -> decoded intent -> mempool/state context -> LLM review -> deterministic policy gate -> transaction builder -> signer -> relay/RPC/private route -> confirmation worker -> Merkle receipt

Policy invariant:
read / observe / simulate / prove = non-consequential
push / schedule / notify / bridge / trade / write = consequential

Safety invariant:
The LLM must not directly sign, submit, or move funds. The LLM classifies and recommends. A deterministic policy engine permits or rejects. A wallet or human approval layer signs.

FORBIDDEN MODES
- sandwich attack
- predatory frontrunning
- spoof liquidity
- oracle manipulation
- exploit of vulnerable contracts
- draining unowned funds

APPRAISAL ROLE
This chat and its attached artifacts are not money by themselves. They are provenance-backed protocol-IP evidence. They become collateralizable only as a package: authored works, source artifacts, Merkle roots, .llm ledgers, screenshots, runtime docs, valuation memo, and deployable prototype pathway.

CAPSULE CLAIM
Overmanifold converts semantic artifacts and observed chain events into addressable endpoint-workers whose provenance, finality, timing, liquidity impact, and routing value can be appraised, recorded, and recursively re-used as network state.
